                <head>24. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At 10 a.m. on October 17, 1962, the Joint Chiefs of Staff met and decided that a
                    surgical strike against the MRBM sites alone represented an unacceptable risk.
                    They incorporated their views in a memorandum to Secretary of Defense <persName
                        corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> (<gloss target="#t_JCSM1"
                        >JCSM</gloss>-794-62;<gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Files), which
                    suggested air attacks on a wide variety of military targets.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
